---
import { blogPosts } from '~/data/rental-x-pages';

const related = blogPosts.slice(1, 4);
---

<main>
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden">
    <img
      src={blogPosts[0].image}
      alt={blogPosts[0].title}
      class="h-[42vh] min-h-[320px] w-full object-cover"
    />
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-black/55"></div>
    <div class="absolute inset-0 flex items-center justify-center px-4 text-white">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-white/70">{blogPosts[0].category}</p>
        <h1 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-semibold leading-tight md:text-5xl">{blogPosts[0].title}</h1>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto grid w-full max-w-6xl gap-8 px-4 pt-12 md:grid-cols-[1.2fr_0.8fr] md:px-6">
    <article class="rounded-3xl border border-black/10 bg-white p-6 md:p-8">
      <p class="text-sm text-black/70">
        A cabin trip works best when you balance adventure, recovery, and flexibility. Plan your essentials around layers,
        weather swings, and at least one low-effort day so the experience stays restorative.
      </p>
      <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl font-semibold">Build a simple day structure</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-black/70">
        Start with a short morning walk, anchor one core activity in the afternoon, and keep evenings open. This approach
        prevents overbooking and gives room for weather changes.
      </p>
      <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl font-semibold">Pack for layered comfort</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-black/70">
        Bring breathable base layers, one warm outer layer, and waterproof shoes. Keep a compact day bag for trail water,
        snacks, and a light first-aid kit.
      </p>
      <blockquote class="mt-8 rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-[#ff4d4d] bg-[#ff4d4d]/10 p-4 text-sm text-black/75">
        The best stays feel unhurried. Leave 20% of your schedule open for spontaneous moments.
      </blockquote>

      <div class="mt-8 rounded-2xl bg-[#ff4d4d] p-6 text-white">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Ready for your own forest escape?</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-white/85">Book your stay and we will help personalize activities before arrival.</p>
        <a href="/rental-x/contact-v1" class="mt-4 inline-flex rounded-full bg-white px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-[#ff4d4d]"
          >Talk to concierge</a
        >
      </div>
    </article>

    <aside class="space-y-6">
      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-black/10 bg-white p-5">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Author</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 flex items-center gap-3">
          <img
            src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1494790108377-be9c29b29330?auto=format&fit=crop&w=300&q=80"
            alt="Author"
            class="h-12 w-12 rounded-full object-cover"
          />
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold">Emma Fielding</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-black/60">Travel writer</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-black/10 bg-white p-5">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Related posts</h2>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-4">
          {
            related.map((post) => (
              <li class="flex gap-3">
                <img src={post.image} alt={post.title} class="h-16 w-16 rounded-xl object-cover" />
                <div>
                  <a href="/rental-x/blog-post" class="text-sm font-semibold hover:underline">{post.title}</a>
                  <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-black/60">{post.date}</p>
                </div>
              </li>
            ))
          }
        </ul>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </section>
</main>
